# Compas Reference
# Time signature: 4/4 (not 12-beat like Bulerias/Solea)
# Character: Upbeat, danceable, rhythmic drive
# Often uses palmas, cajon, or full rhythm section

# Scale Reference
# A Phrygian Dominant (5th mode of D harmonic minor)
# A-Bb-C#-D-E-F-G
# The raised 3rd (C# vs C) gives the exotic Spanish flavor
# Tritone: C#-G (3rd & b7 of A7) resolves to D minor

# Zone-Tritone Connection
# bII -> I (Bb -> A) is a ZONE-CROSSING half-step resolution
# A=9(Z2), Bb=10(Z1) -- zone cross creates gravitational pull
# This is the "Phrygian Gravity Cell"

# Harmony Reference
# Key: A Phrygian Dominant (A-Bb-C#-D-E-F-G)
# Typical chords: A(I) - Bb(bII) - Dm(iv) - A(I)
# The A major chord in minor context = exotic color
# Parent scale: D harmonic minor (A7 is V7 of Dm)

